# PROMPT_LOG.md

## Prompt 1 – Initial UI Generation

I provided the AI with the assignment description and the reference screenshots of the scheduler UI (similar to Calendly). I asked:

"Using React, help me build a meeting scheduler interface similar to the reference images. The layout should have a calendar on the left and available time slots on the right. Users should be able to select a date and then pick a time slot."

---

## Prompt 2 – Time Slot Generation

After setting up the calendar component, I Prompted,

"I need to generate 15-minute meeting slots between 9 AM and 5 PM. Can you help me write a JavaScript function that creates these time slots and displays them as selectable buttons?"

---

## Prompt 3 – Booking Form

Once the time slot selection was working, I asked:

"After the user selects a time slot, I want to navigate to a booking form. The form should collect the user's first name, surname, and email address. It should also display the selected date, time, and meeting location (Google Meet). Can you generate the React component for this?"

---

## Prompt 4 – Confirmation Screen

"Create a confirmation screen that appears after the user submits the booking form. The screen should display the meeting details such as date, time, timezone, and a Google Meet link. It should also show a confirmation message."

---
## Prompt 5 – Email Notification Simulation

"I need to simulate a confirmation email after a meeting is booked. The simulated email should include the attendee's email, meeting date and time with timezone, a Google Meet link, and action buttons for rescheduling or cancelling."

---
## Prompt 6 – Layout Improvements

While styling the interface, I prompted:

"Based on the reference screenshots of the scheduler UI, help me improve the layout so that the calendar and time slots appear side-by-side on desktop and look visually clean."

---
## Prompt 7 – Responsive Design

Finally, I asked the AI:

"Help me make the layout responsive so the scheduler works well on both desktop and mobile screens."
